STEP|27|TOON only compresses INPUT.** The LLM's response (completion) tokens are unchanged unless you also compress output. This is the single most important thing to understand ‚Äî and the #1 reason users say 
STEP|28|The brutal truth:** On reasoning tasks where the LLM's response IS the deliverable, you cannot compress the value. TOON saves on context injection, not on thinking. Tell users this upfront or they wil
STEP|29|NEVER use compression on small datasets.** Overhead dominates below 15 items.
STEP|30|NEVER claim 80% savings on reasoning tasks.** That's prompt-only; total tokens tell the real story.
STEP|31|Why:** Dictionary/template definitions cost ~400 tokens in system prompt overhead. On 3-item tasks, that's MORE than the savings. Break-even is ~15 items where savings exceed overhead.
STEP|32|Output compression:** Ask the LLM to respond in structured format (`id\|action\|reason`) instead of prose. This cuts completion tokens by 60%+ on data tasks. On reasoning tasks, do NOT compress output
