STEP|38|‚öÝÔ∏è HONESTY CHECK:** These are REASONING tasks where the LLM wrote 4,000-5,000 character strategic memos. The output IS the value ‚Äî you cannot compress it. The 29.4% total savings is real and valuable,
STEP|39|NEVER send template IDs to the LLM.** The compressor must RESOLVE templates inline before sending. The LLM receives the full resolved text, not `t1` or `{p}` placeholders.
STEP|40|WRONG:** `D\|d001\|0\|0\|t1\|C\|0` ‚Äî LLM sees template ID, guesses values
STEP|41|RIGHT:** `D\|d001\|0\|0\|Stripe raised fees 15%: 12450txns/mo\|C\|0` ‚Äî LLM sees real data
STEP|42|**Users will say "not impressed" if you quote prompt-only savings.** Always report TOTAL token savings (prompt + completion). The 61.4% prompt-only figure on the Stripe crisis was actually 29.4% total
STEP|43|**Template IDs cause hallucinations** ‚Äî NEVER send `t1`, `t2` to LLM. Always resolve templates inline first. The LLM will guess values if it sees placeholders. Proven in benchmark: LLM guessed $50 avg
STEP|44|**Positional fragility** ‚Äî if field order changes in `dense()`, all consumers break. Never reorder schema fields without updating all callers.
STEP|45|**Compression overhead** ‚Äî dictionary/template definitions cost ~400 tokens. On ‚â§10 item tasks, overhead > savings. Use adaptive selection.
STEP|46|**Output compression is task-dependent** ‚Äî asking for TOON output on a strategic memo destroys the value (the prose IS the answer). Only use bidirectional on structured data tasks (filtering, classifi
STEP|47|**Pipe in text** ‚Äî must be escaped as `\\|` in pipe formats. `toon.dense()` handles this automatically.
STEP|48|**Not for external APIs** ‚Äî only use TOON internally between YVON OS components and LLM prompts.
STEP|49|**Claude vs DeepSeek** ‚Äî `toon.claude()` format is designed for Claude's prose-optimized tokenizer. On DeepSeek, `toon.dense()` is better.
STEP|50|**Always verify with real API calls** ‚Äî tokenizer estimates (tiktoken) differ from actual API token counts. The live benchmarks in references/benchmarks.md are the source of truth.
STEP|51|**Small datasets need TOON, not compression** ‚Äî the break-even where compression beats plain TOON is ~15 items.
STEP|52|**Benchmark on REAL workloads, not synthetic ones.** Run benchmarks on the actual agent cron tasks (Henry filtering 50 real decisions), not contrived 3-item examples. The savings profiles are dramatic
STEP|53|**ALL agent data uses `toon.dense()` or compressor** ‚Äî never raw JSON
STEP|54|**Adaptive selection:** ‚â§10 items ‚Üí toon.dense, 10-30 ‚Üí +dictionary, 30+ ‚Üí +templates, repeat ‚Üí delta
STEP|55|**Templates must be RESOLVED before sending to LLM** ‚Äî never send template IDs
STEP|56|**API responses default to JSON** ‚Äî add `?format=toon` for agent consumers
STEP|57|**dataBlock field** on `ClaudeRequestBody` is the injection point
STEP|58|**System prompt auto-injects TOON parsing instruction** when dataBlock is present
